The reports suggest that the nature of the violence, which includes sexual attacks and dismemberment, could constitute crimes against humanity. Examining events in DRC's Ituri province between December 2017 and September 2019, they said much of the violence was carried out by the Lendu community, with the aim of creating terror among the Hema, so they would not return to their land. The UN has called on DRC to address the land-related causes of the conflict and urged the UN's stabilisation force to extend its military presence in Ituri. --BBC--